===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|non|en}}, akin to Swedish {{m|sv|basa||to baste, whip, lash, flog}}, Danish {{m|da|baske||to beat, strike, cudgel}}, German {{m|de|patschen||to slap}}<ref>{{R:ODS online|baske}}</ref>.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|es}}

# To [[strike]] heavily.
#: {{ux|en|He '''bashed''' himself against the door.}}
#: {{ux|en|The thugs kept '''bashing''' the [[cower]]ing victim.}}
# To [[collide]].
#: {{ux|en|Don't '''bash''' into me with that [[shopping trolley]].}}
# To [[criticize]] [[harsh]]ly.
#: {{ux|en|He '''bashed''' my [[idea]]s.}}

